#%Module1.0

module-whatis       "Custom modification of AlphaFold 3 enabling explicit modeling of crosslinks."
module-url          "https://github.com/KosinskiLab/af3x"
module-license	    "Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International"
module-maintainer   "Jo√£o Pedro Agostinho de Sousa <joao.agostinho-de-sousa@psi.ch>"

module-help         "
Most crosslink-based modeling programs implicitly model crosslinks by adding
distance restraints between crosslinked residues. This program explicitly
models crosslinks by adding crosslinker molecules as ligands and setting bonds
to the crosslinked residues. This allows for more realistic modeling of
crosslinks, and sometimes gives good results. The results are also more
visually appealing.
"

# Environment variables
setenv APPTAINER_IMAGE /data/project/bio/shared/containers/af3x/dev/af3x.sif
setenv PUBLIC_DATABASES_DIR /data/project/bio/shared/alphafold3/public_databases
